# ENV_NAME=Staging
# SITE_URL=https://your-staging-site.org

# ====================
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES
# ====================
# 1. .env files contain sensitive credentials - NEVER commit them
# 2. Each environment has separate .env files (.env, .env.production, .env.staging)
# 3. .gitignore blocks all .env* files from being committed
# 4. Server-side .env files (on production/staging servers) contain database credentials
# 5. Local .env files contain SSH credentials for deployment
# 6. Always use /deploy-production and /deploy-staging skills for safe deployments
